&quot;For young people in communities where there are no branch libraries -- The Bronx Traveling Library.&quot;

I really  like the design of this bookmobile -- flaps on the sides open upward to reveal shelves of books, so people can browse without going inside.

I'm a librarian, an I love looking at old library photographs, especially ones showing library extension and outreach. I love helping to bring digital resources to library users, but I think that we could do more to bring real books and real librarians to people outside of our library buildings.
